24.0.0 RADIOACTIVITY (10 Lessons)
24.1.0 Specific Objectives
By the end of this topic, the leamer
should be able to:
a) define radioactivity, half-life,
radioisotope and nuclides
b) state types of radioactivity
c) name the particles emitted
during radioactive decay and
state their properties
d) carry out simple calculations
involving half-life (1/2)
e) write balanced nuclear
equations

fission and fusion

radioisotopes
